In a conciliatory tone, Governor Kiraitu said he is keen on working closely with all Meru leaders.Meru Woman Rep Kawira Mwangaza and Eala MP Mpuru Aburi said they are not ready to settle their differences with the governor. Meru Governor Kiraitu Murungi has extended an olive branch to his rivals as he seeks to solidify his political base ahead of his 2022 re-election bid.
In a New Year message, Governor Kiraitu said part of his 2021 resolutions is to mend fences with Meru Woman Representative Kawira Mwangaza, East African Legislative Assembly (Eala) MP Mpuru Aburi and other political rivals.



