The two politicians have been a pain in Mr Kiraitu’s governorship, with several public spats being witnessed in 2020.
Ms Mwangaza has since announced she will run against Mr Kiraitu in the 2022 gubernatorial contest while Mr Aburi, a friend-turned-foe, is drumming up support for the governor’s main rival, Agriculture Cabinet Secretary Peter Munya.
But, in a conciliatory tone, Governor Kiraitu said he is keen on working closely with all Meru leaders, adding that “living in conflict with others is like chasing the wind.”



