“As part of my new year resolutions, I intend to have a cup of tea with my political rivals and extend my friendships. I will engage Kawira Mwangaza to see what it is we are fighting about. This will ensure we perform our duties without fighting each other. I will also look for Aburi so that we mend fences,” the governor said in an interview with a local TV station.
He said he will work hard this year to encourage amicable resolution of differences among political leaders since it is the last opportunity to deliver on development.
“I will also meet the members of county assembly to chart the way forward,” he said.
Political enmity 
In the last three years, Governor Kiraitu has been working hard to assimilate his political rivals, including raiding CS Munya’s camp.



